<<<explanation>>>: StringTokenizer st = new StringTokenizer(words, ",");
This will create a StringTokenizer object with the string words and the delimiter ",".
String words1[] = new String[st.countTokens()];
This will create an array of strings with the same number of elements as the number of tokens in the string.
int i = 0;
This will create a variable i that will be used to keep track of the current index in the array.
while (st.hasMoreTokens()) {
words1[i] = st.nextToken();
i++;
}
This will loop through the tokens in the string and assign each token to the corresponding element in the array.
The code will create an array of strings with the same number of elements as the number of tokens in the string.
